Greater demon ash lords are monsters released with The Zamorakian Undercity.

They can also be found in the Wilderness, east of the Demonic Ruins alongside greater demon berserkers. The demons in the elite dungeon are immune to stun and poison, whereas the Wilderness demons have less health and are susceptible to both stun and poison.

Like their fellow demons encountered in the elite dungeon, these monsters are capable of pathing around obstacles to reach the player (including in the Wilderness) and can deal immense amounts of damage with their magic attacks. They may be killed in place of a greater demon task for more slayer experience. Each kill reduces the task count by 8.

Mechanics[edit | edit source]

This type of greater demon possesses the Strong guard status, which makes the players' attacks incapable of missing; however, their accuracy will affect the damage they deal.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 3 April 2023 (Update):
    • Adjusted the spawn location of demons at the bloodwood tree west of the Dragonkin Laboratory as they often interfered with players interacting with the tree.
  • patch 13 March 2023 (Update):
    • Moved the berserkers from the area near the level 44 Wilderness obelisk to area outside the Dragonkin Laboratory.
  • patch 5 September 2022 (Update):
    • Updated the Greater Demons in Wilderness:
      • Reduced health of ash lords from 140,000 to 110,000.
      • Removed stun and poison immunity.
      • Added drops.
  • update 1 August 2022 (Update):
    • Added to Wilderness.
  • update 4 July 2022 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Alongside the berserkers, the greater demon ash lord are the first monsters to drop necronium salvage.
